videoSnippet.title: God Of Bullet Returns | Magnus Carlsen Wins 6th Lichess Titled Arena
videoSnippet.description:
#agadmator

Check out this game on Andrew Tang's channel here https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nmd5EbYueYM - starts around 22 min mark.

Tournament link here https://lichess.org/tournament/3ImmfhBr
Link to this game here https://lichess.org/D1I97F3Y

Andrew Tang (GM penguinim1) vs Magnus Carlsen (GM damnsaltythatsport)
6th Lichess Titled Arena - 5th Aug (2018) 
Benoni Defense: Czech variation (A56)

1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 c5 3. d5 e5 4. Nc3 d6 5. e4 g6 6. g3 Bg7 7. Bg2 O-O 8. Nge2 Nbd7 9. O-O a6 10. a4 Nh5 11. f4 exf4 12. gxf4 f5 13. exf5 Rxf5 14. Be3 Ndf6 15. Ng3 Nxg3 16. hxg3 Rh5 17. Bf3 Rh3 18. Kg2 h5 19. Qd2 h4 20. gxh4 Nh5 21. Rh1 Qxh4 22. Ne4 Bg4 23. Qf2 Qxf2+ 24. Nxf2 Rg3+ 25. Kf1 Rxf3 26. Re1 Ng3+ 27. Kg2 Nxh1 28. Nxg4 Rg3+ 29. Kxh1 Rxg4

lichess.org is a free/libre, open-source chess server powered by volunteers and donations.

In 2010, Thibault Duplessis began work on Lichess as a hobby project. The site was simple in the beginning, not even checking to see if moves were legal. He made the site open-source, which means anyone is free to read the source code and make contributions. Gradually, the site improved and collected users as an enthusiastic volunteer staff assembled to help Thibault build and maintain the site.

Read more about Lichess here: https://lichess.org/about
